  "body": "If you do something like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nawait expect(contract.f()).to.emit(contract, \"MyEvent\").withArgs(2);\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou get this error message:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      AssertionError: expected 1 to equal 2. The numerical values of the given \"ethers.BigNumber\" and \"number\" inputs were compared, and they differed.\r\n      + expected - actual\r\n\r\n      -1\r\n      +2\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut the message doesn't say anything about the assertion. It should include the fact that it's talking about an event, and include the name of the event. Something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      AssertionError: expected 1 to equal 2 in the first argument of the 'MyEvent' event. The numerical values of the given \"ethers.BigNumber\" and \"number\" inputs were compared, and they differed.\r\n      + expected - actual\r\n\r\n      -1\r\n      +2\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm also not convinced about the mentions of the types; that seems like an implementation detail we shouldn't show.\r\n\r\nThe same thing happens with the `revertedWithCustomError` matcher, and we should fix that too.\r\n\r\ncc @shark0der",
